definitions.definition: Indefinite article used before singular nouns
definitions.example: I saw a bird
Aah! That's amazing!

definitions.definition: To exclaim with joy or surprise
definitions.example: The crowd aahed at the fireworks
They aahed in delight
She was aahing at the cute puppies

definitions.definition: Plural form of 'aah' as a noun

definitions.example: He aahs every time he sees candy

definitions.definition: Nocturnal African mammal that eats ants
definitions.example: The aardvark dug for termites
Aargh! I stubbed my toe!

definitions.definition: Relating to Aaron, the biblical figure
In Egyptian mythology, the heavenly paradise
Plural of 'aa', a type of lava
Type of fabric made from goat or camel hair
Philippine banana plant yielding Manila hemp

definitions.example: The ancient Romans used abaci for calculations.

definitions.definition: To blind by holding a red-hot metal plate before the eyes
The act of blinding someone with intense light or heat
Person skilled in using an abacus

definitions.example: I was taken aback by the news.

definitions.definition: With sails pressed backward against the mast
Opposite to the mouth (in starfish and other echinoderms)
The stealing of cattle in herds
One who steals cattle in large numbers
Calculating tool with beads sliding on rods
definitions.example: Children learn math using an abacus.

definitions.definition: Architectural element atop a column capital
Biblical name for the place of destruction
Spanish term for codfish or pollock
definitions.example: El abadejo es un pescado blanco muy popular en España.

definitions.definition: Relating to an abbot or abbey
Descendant of Abad, an Arabic name
Nautical term meaning toward the stern
Behind or toward the rear of a ship
definitions.example: The lifeboats are stored abaft the funnel.

definitions.definition: Obsolete term for barking or a bark
Traditional Arabic cloak worn by women
Obsolete form of obeisance (a bow or gesture of respect)
Ivory black pigment made from charred ivory
Thin pastry dough used as base in cooking
Alternative spelling of abaca (Manila hemp plant)
To transfer legal title of property
Edible sea mollusk with a ear-shaped shell lined with mother-of-pearl
definitions.example: We harvested abalone off the California coast.

definitions.definition: Genus of large tropical American butterflies
Unit of electric current in the electromagnetic CGS system (equal to 10 amperes)

definitions.example: They had to abandon the sinking ship.
She abandoned herself to grief.
He danced with wild abandon.

abandon.etymology: From Old French 'abandoner', from 'a bandon' (at one's disposal)

definitions.example: An abandoned factory stood at the edge of town.
Abandoned behavior at the party

definitions.definition: In an abandoned manner; without restraint
One to whom something is formally abandoned (especially in insurance)

definitions.example: The abandonment of the project disappointed many.

definitions.definition: Legal term for property to be abandoned
One who abases or humiliates others
To cause to feel embarrassed or ashamed
Inability to walk due to impaired coordination
A historical silver coin used in Persia.
definitions.example: The merchant paid with an abassi.

abassi.etymology: From Persian عباسی ('abbāsī), named after Shah Abbas I.

definitions.example: The abassin was used in trade.
The abastard lineage lost its prestige.

definitions.definition: To corrupt or debase in lineage or character.
definitions.example: The family was abastardized by generations of poor alliances.

definitions.definition: To reduce in amount, degree, or intensity.
definitions.example: The storm began to abate by evening.

definitions.definition: To put an end to or nullify.
definitions.example: The court abated the lawsuit.
There was an abate in taxes this year.

abate.etymology: From Old French 'abatre', meaning 'to beat down'.

definitions.definition: The act or process of reducing.
definitions.example: Noise abatement measures were implemented.

definitions.definition: A defensive obstacle made of felled trees with sharpened branches.
definitions.example: The soldiers constructed an abatis to block the road.

definitions.definition: Capable of being abated or reduced.
definitions.example: The nuisance was abatable by legal action.

definitions.definition: A device, such as a skylight or reflector, used to direct light into a room.
definitions.example: The attic was lit by an abatjour.
The abated winds made sailing easier.

definitions.definition: Present participle of 'abate'; reducing in intensity.
definitions.example: The storm is abating slowly.
